  "description": "¶Entry conditions You should know the definition of a vector space and be comfortable with bases and dimension.\n¶Definitions A linear map (or linear transformation) T:V→WT : V \\to W between vector spaces over the same field preserves addition and scalar multiplication: T(u+v)=T(u)+T(v)T(\\mathbf{u} + \\mathbf{v}) = T(\\mathbf{u}) + T(\\mathbf{v}) and T(av)=aT(v)T(a\\mathbf{v}) = aT(\\mathbf{v}).\nGiven bases for VV and WW, every linear map corresponds to a matrix — a rectangular array of scalars. Composing linear maps corresponds to multiplying their matrices.\n",
